t%20concentration%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenwich%20and%20Stamford%2C%20a%20pair%20of%20bedroom%20communities%20of%20the%20New%20York%20metro%2C%20have%20also%20continued%20to%20be%20important%20centers%20of%20gravity%20for%20hedge%20funds%2C%20which%20have%20become%20a%20part%20of%20the%20social%20fabric%20of%20these%20Connecticut%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECitadel's%20talent%20breakdown%2C%20according%20to%20its%20ADV%20showing%20data%20from%20last%20March%2C%20is%20interesting%20given%20the%20firm's%20billionaire%20founder's%20preference%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitadel-headquarters-in-miami-work-life-balance-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMiami%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ken%20Griffin%2C%20who%20is%20originally%20from%20Florida%2C%20moved%20his%20firm's%20headquarters%20south%20from%20Chicago%20in%202022%20and%20has%20commented%20that%20one%20day%2C%20the%20city%20could%20surpass%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbillionaire-ken-griffin-miami-will-overtake-new-york-finance-hub-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20as%20a%20financial%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20though%20he%20still%20referred%20to%20Manhattan%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bepicenter%20of%20thoughtful%20people%20passionately%20engaged%20in%20their%20careers%26quot%3B%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Griffin%20and%20some%20of%20his%20executives%2C%20including%20chief%20risk%20officer%20Joanna%20Welsh%20and%20commodities%20head%20Sebastian%20Barrack%2C%20have%20relocated%2C%20the%20firm's%20investing%20talent%20has%20not%20yet%20moved%20en%20masse%20to%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20showed%20that%20more%20investment-focused%20staffers%20were%20based%20in%20the%20firm's%20two%20Texas%20offices%2C%20Houston%20and%20Dallas%2C%20than%20in%20its%20two%20Sunshine%20State%20offices%2C%20Miami%20and%20Tampa.%20The%20%2466%20billion%20fund%20has%20more%20investors%20in%20each%20of%20its%20two%20New%20Y