%20from%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20work%20%3Cem%3Ecan't%20%3C%2Fem%3Eprovide%20them%3F%20Maybe%20it's%20not%20that%20they're%20lazy%20or%20entitled.%20Maybe%20they're%20just%20unwilling%20to%20endure%20all%20the%20shitty%20stuff%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20job%20in%20return%20for%20an%20elusive%20payoff%20decades%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20work%20has%20always%20been%20a%20drag%20%E2%80%94%20difficult%2C%20dull%2C%20and%20demanding.%20That's%20why%20they%20call%20it%20%3Cem%3Ework.%3C%2Fem%3E%20But%20for%20previous%20generations%2C%20there%20were%20enticements%20that%20made%20the%20daily%20grind%20seem%20worth%20it.%20For%20boomers%2C%20the%20prize%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifetime%20of%20job%20security%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20it%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareerist-corporate-ladder-decline-promotions-work-ethic-american-dream-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprestige%20of%20a%20corner%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20millennials%2C%20it%20was%20fulfilling%20your%20true%20potential%20and%20making%20the%20world%20a%20better%20place.%20Whatever%20their%20dreams%2C%20each%20generation%20worked%20for%20years%20before%20they%20discovered%20that%20the%20rewards%20they'd%20been%20promised%20in%20return%20for%20their%20effort%20often%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20mirage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Zers%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20seem%20to%20have%20grasped%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-college-students-renege-job-offers-tech-rescinded-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransactional%20nature%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20very%20outset.%20They%20don't%20have%20any%20of%20the%20naive%20expectations%20about%20employment%20that%20I%20did%20when%20I%20was%20their%20age.%20They've%20seen%20their%20parents%20work%20for%20years%20in%20soul-deadening%20jobs%2C%20only%20to%20wind%20up%20without%20enough%20to%20retire.%20They%20get%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehustle%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-women-executives-hustle-culture-girlboss-work-life-balance-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20they%20know%20that%20no%20amount%20of%20putting%20up%20with%20shit%20at%20work%20will%20protect%20them%20from%20being%20shitcanned.%20They're%20disengaged%20at%20work%20because%20they%20don't%20trust%20that%20they'll%20be%20rewarded%20for%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20so%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20focused%20on%20side%20hustles%3A%20They're%20so%20fed%20up%20with%20their%20employers%20that%20they'd%20rather%20be%20their%20own%20boss.%20It%20also%20explains%20why%20they're%20captivated%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFIRE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20viral%20movement%20that's%20short%20for%20financial%20independence%2C%20retire%20early.%20Just%20a%20few%20years%20into%20their%20careers%2C%20they're%20already%20dreaming%20of%20the%20day%20they'll%20be%20free%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20should%20employers%20do%2C%20given%20Gen%20Z's%20startling%20level%20of%20disengagement%3F%20First%20off%2C%20don't%20order%20everyone%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20As%20I%20wrote%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20research%20shows%20that%20RTO%20edicts%20only%20demoralize%20everyone%20even%20more.%20Instead%2C%20employers%20need%20to%20be%20more%20intentional%20about%20designing%20jobs%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20their%20junior%20staff.%20They%20can't%20leave%20things%20like%20mentoring%20and%20networking%20to%20chance%2C%20the%20way%20they%20did%20when%20the%20office%20forced%20everyone%20into%20proximity.%20They%20also%20need%20to%20provide%20employees%20with%20more%20predictability%20and%20stability%2C%20rather%20than%20swinging%20from%20extreme%20to%20extreme%20the%20way%20they've%20been%20doing%20with%20remote%20work%20and%20diversity%20initiatives.%20And%20to%20ease%20the%20AI%20anxieties%20of%20their%20young%20employees%2C%20companies%20should%20focus%20on%20implementing%20technology%20that%20assists%20their%20staff%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20replacing%20them%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20steps%20would%20help.%20But%20to%20truly%20engage%20their%20youngest%20workers%2C%20companies%20need%20to%20give%20them%20a%20concrete%20reason%20to%20be%20excited%20about%20their%20jobs.%20They%20can%20shape%20assignments%20to%20each%20employee's%20interests%20and%20goals%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20ways%20to%20vary%20the%20tasks%20within%20each%20role%2C%20so%20an%20employee%20isn't%20stuck%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20over%20and%20over.%20They%20can%20crack%20down%20on%20toxic%20managers%2C%20and%20offer%20employees%20a%20little%20more%20freedom%20to%20choose%20%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20do%20their%20jobs.%20And%20they%20can%20cultivate%20a%20corporate%20culture%20that%20encourages%20even%20entry-level%20employees%20to%20contribute%20ideas%20and%20provide%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20will%20happen%20only%20if%20managers%20actually%20listen%20to%20everyone's%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20about%20catering%20to%20the%20whims%20of%20Gen%20Z.%20These%20are%20the%20tried-and-true%20ways%2C%20backed%20by%20decades%20of%20rigorous%20research%2C%20to%20create%20more%20engaging%20jobs%20for%20everyone%2C%20regardless%20of%20age.%20Making%20jobs%20more%20interesting%20will%20motivate%20the%20entire%20workforce.%20And%20there's%20nothing%20fluffy%20about%20making%20employees%20hap