s-and-the-other-right-wing-in-silicon-valley-set-to-drive-policy-in-donald-trumps-government%2Farticleshow%2F117598459.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Is%20Trump%20Serious%20About%20Annexing%20Canada%3F%20Or%20Is%20He%20Just%20Being%20Trump%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20during%20my%20one%20and%20only%20trip%20to%20Pakistan%20to%20report%20on%20the%2050th%20anniversary%20of%20independence%20for%20a%20Western%20media%20outlet%2C%20I%20had%20the%20pleasure%20of%20meeting%20some%20bright%2C%20articulate%20students%20at%20the%20famed%20Government%20College%20in%20Lahore.%20Feeling%20magnanimous%20(and%20admittedly%20swept%20by%20their%20genuine%20warmth)%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20drop%20a%20bombshell%20of%20an%20idea%3A%20why%20not%20reunite%20India%20and%20Pakistan%3F%20Should%20we%20not%20right%20the%20wrongs%20of%20Partition%2C%20restore%20the%20subcontinent%20to%20its%20undivided%20glory%2C%20and%20perhaps%20save%20on%20visa%20fees%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20reaction%20shook%20me%20up%20no%20end.%20Polite%20smiles%20laced%20with%20a%20palpable%20%E2%80%98what-is-this-guy-talking-about%3F'.%20Most%20of%20them%20agreed%20that%20Partition%20was%20a%20disaster%E2%80%94but%2C%20they%20were%20quick%20to%20add%2C%20not%20%3Cem%3Etheir%20%3C%2Fem%3Edisaster.%20The%20blame%2C%20they%20insisted%2C%20lay%20squarely%20with%20the%20Urdu-speaking%20folks%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20had%20fled%20to%20Karachi%20and%20now%20live%20as%20'%3Cem%3Emuhajir%3C%2Fem%3E'%20(immigrants).%20One%20student%20practically%20bristled%20at%20my%20proposal%20and%20said%20my%20suggestion%20reeked%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctypical%20Indian%20response%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20post-Partition%20generation%2C%20which%20was%20a%20rather%20diplomatic%20way%20of%20calling%20me%20na%C3%AFve.%20I%20get%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20their%20post-Partition%20Pakistani%20perspective%2C%20the%20students%20argued%2C%20reunification%20was%20a%20no-go.%20Sure%2C%20their%20country%20wasn't%20perfect%E2%80%94admittedly%20not%20on%20a%20par%20with%20India%E2%80%94but%20it%20was%20their%20own.%20Sovereign%2C%20independent%2C%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20theirs%20to%20nurture%20or%20mess%20up%2C%20without%20unsolicited%20advice%20from%20nostalgic%20neighbours%20across%20the%20border.%20The%20message%20was%20clear%3A%20the%20idea%20of%20negating%20Partition%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20silly%20they%20thought%20it%20was%2C%20wasn't%20up%20for%20debate.%20Period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20perspective%20that%20had%20never%20crossed%20my%20Indian-bred%20mind.%20It%20reminded%20me%20of%20the%20shock%20Canadians%20are%20feeling%20at%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20latest%20shenanigan%E2%80%94his%20not-so-casual%20declaration%20that%20he%20would%20like%20to%20annex%20Canada%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20America's%2051st%20state.%20Last%20week%2C%20Trump%2C%20always%20a%20fan%20of%20the%20spotlight%2C%20used%20an%20international%20platform%20to%20float%20the%20idea.%20Addressing%20the%20Davos%20economic%20forum%20via%20video%20link%2C%20he%20coolly%20tossed%20out%20the%20notion%20to%20an%20audience%20of%20CEOs%20and%20business%20honchos.%20Predictably%2C%20gasps%20echoed%20through%20the%20room.%20And%20somewhere%20in%20Ottawa%2C%20I%20imagine%2C%20jaws%20hit%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20surprising%20isn't%20just%20the%20audacity%20of%20Trump's%20suggestion%20but%20the%20sheer%20persistence%20of%20it.%20His%20rhetorical%20swipes%20at%20Canada's%20independence%20have%20become%20so%20frequent%20that%20one%20wonders%20if%20he%20is%20genuinely%20serious%20or%20just%20bored%20with%20his%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US-Canada%20overlap%20is%20everywhere%E2%80%94from%20culture%20to%20sports%20to%20shared%20traditions.%20Neighbours%20for%20sure%2C%20but%20they%20are%20more%20like%20squabbling%20siblings.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20US-Canada%20trade%20hit%20over%20a%20trillion%20dollars%2C%20with%20%242.8%20billion%20crossing%20their%20border%20every%20single%20day.%20They%20are%20each%20other's%20biggest%20trade%20partners%2C%20with%20Canada%20sending%2078%25%20of%20its%20goods%20and%20services%20to%20the%20US%20every%20year%2C%20and%20over%204%2C00%2C000%20people%20moving%20across%20their%20shared%205%2C525-mile%20border%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'No%2C%20Thanks'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reactions%20to%20Trump's%20comments%20range%20from%20polite%20Canadian%20indignation%20to%20outright%20laughter.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Americans%20seem%20split%20between%20%E2%80%9CWait%2C%20can%20we%20actually%20do%20that%3F%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20would%20we%20even%20want%20to%3F%E2%80%9D.%20Let's%20unpack%20these%20views%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20BuzzFeed%20ran%20an%20article%20that%20asked%20Canadians%20about%20their%20thoughts%20on%20Trump's%20eyebrow-raising%20proposal%20to%20annex%20Canada%20as%20America's%2051st%20state.%20Unsurprisingly%2C%20the%20responses%20were%20a%20mixed%20bag%2C%20though%20they%20leaned%20heavily%20towards%20a%20polite%20but%20firm%20%E2%80%9CNo%2C%20thanks%E2%80%9D.%20Here's%20what%20some%20of%20them%20had%20to%20say%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20want%20to%20be%20American.%20No%20one%20I%20know%20wants%20to%20be%20American.%20I%20am%20not%20giving%20up%20my%20free%20healthcare%20and%20strict%20gun%20laws.%20And%20I%20am%20definitely%20not%20giving%20up%20my%20right%20to%20choose%20as%20a%20woman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20rather%20take%20my%20son%20on%20a%20vacation%20to%20Europe%20for%20fear%20of%20our%20safety%20in%20the%20US.%20Your%20lax%20gun%20laws%20make%20me%20afraid%20that%20we%20could%20be%20shot%20while%20vacationing%20in%20any%20part%20of%20your%20country.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20America.%20We%20never%20will%20be.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20America%20would%20benefit%20from%20a%20more%20Canadian%20viewpoint.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BAmericans%20would%20be%20better%20off%20joining%20Canada%20than%20Canadians%20would%20be%20joining%20the%20USA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20of%20course%2C%20there%20were%20those%20I%20would%20call%20%E2%80%98dissenters'.%20Their%20voices%20often%20stemmed%20from%20frustration%20with%20their%20own%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Justin%20Trudeau%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20overwhelming%20love%20for%20Trump's%20America.%20A%20few%20highlights%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BAsk%20me%2015%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20I%20would%20have%20been%20ready%20to%20take%20up%20arms%20against%20any%20US%20threat%3B%20now%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure.%20The%20Liberal%20government%2C%20led%20by%20Trudeau%2C%20has%20divided%20and%20nearly%20destroyed%20our%20culture%20with%20'woke%20ideology'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20be%20the%20first%20one%20to%20vote%20to%20become%20part%20of%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20be%20over%20the%20moon%20to%20become%20an%20American.%20The%20US%20is%20the%20greatest%20country%20in%20the%20world.%20Canada%20has%20been%20riding%20their%20coattails%20for%20years.%20To%20be%20annexed%20into%20the%20US%20would%20be%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20enthusiasm%20must%20be%20appreciated.%20Sure%2C%20they%20might%20get%20Florida%2C%20but%20they%20are%20also%20signing%20up%20for%20the%20'Florida%20Man'.%20And%20they%20are%20happy%20with%20it.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20while%20some%20Canadians%20may%20be%20open%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20annexation%2C%20the%20overwhelming%20sentiment%20seems%20to%20be%2C%20%E2%80%9CThanks%2C%20but%20we're%20good.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20public%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20isn't%20exactly%20rolling%20out%20the%20red%20carpet%20for%20Trump's%20latest%20brainwave.%20Surveys%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EReuters-Ipsos%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist-YouGov%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94all%20conducted%20in%20recent%20days%E2%80%94indicate%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20annexing%20Canada%20is%20about%20as%20popular%20as%20a%20snowstorm%20in%20July.%20So%2C%20we%20must%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20Trump's%20land%20of%20the%20free%20isn't%20exactly%20clamouring%20for%20a%20new%20northern%20star%20on%20its%20flag%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Rare%20Precedent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnnexing%20a%20nation%20without%20a%20war%20is%20a%20rare%20feat%2C%20but%20history%20offers%20a%20few%20eyebrow-raising%20precedents%20that%20might%20bolster%20Trump's%20audacious%20ambitions.%20Consider%20Texas%20in%201845%3A%20the%20Republic%20of%20Texas%20willingly%20joined%20the%20United%20States%20after%20breaking%20free%20from%20Mexico.%20Then%20there%20was%20Hawaii%20in%201898%2C%20annexed%20through%20a%20joint%20resolution%20of%20Congress%20following%20the%20not-so-gentle%20overthrow%20of%20its%20monarchy.%20Both%20cases%2C%20of%20course%2C%20were%20dripping%20with%20controversy%20and%20tangled%20in%20political%20gymnastics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20President%20Trump%20were%20to%20actually%20chase%20his%20dream%20of%20annexing%20Canada%20as%20the%2051st%20state%2C%20he%20would%20be%20plunging%20into%20a%20legal%20and%20political%20minefield.%20For%20starters%2C%20Canada's%20Constitution%20is%20as%20silent%20as%20a%20winter%20morning%20on%20how%20a%20province%E2%80%94or%20the%20entire%20nation%2C%20for%20that%20matter%E2%80%94could%20secede%20and%20join%20another%20country.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20the%20US%20Constitution%20does%20allow%20for%20new%20states%20to%20join%20with%20Congressional%20approval%2C%20but%20annexing%20a%20fully%20sovereign%20country%20is%20uncharted%20territory%2C%20legally%20speaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20political%20and%20populist%20angle.%20Agreed%20that%20Trump's%20statement%20might%20strike%20a%20chord%20with%20certain%20populist%20audiences.%20But%20the%20logistics%20of%20such%20an%20annexation%20are%20a%20Herculean%20challenge.%20The%20deeply%20entrenched%20national%20identities%20and%20legal%20frameworks%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20border%20make%20this%20idea%20more%20rhetorical%20than%20realistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInto%20Trump's%20Mind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20himself%20drops%20plenty%20of%20hints%20about%20how%20he%20views%20his%20annexation%20dream.%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20also%20considering%20military%20force%20to%20annex%20and%20acquire%20Canada%3F%26quot%3B%20a%20reporter%20asked%20him%20recently.%20%E2%80%9CNo.%20Economic%20force%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20promptly.%20%E2%80%9CCanada%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20that%20would%20really%20be%20something.%20You%20get%20rid%20of%20that%20artificially%20drawn%20line%2C%20and%20you%20take%20a%20look%20at%20what%20that%20looks%20like%2C%20and%20it%20would%20also%20be%20much%20better%20for%20national%20security.%20Don't%20forget%2C%20we%20basically%20protect%20Canada.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustin%20Trudeau%2C%20who%20is%20stepping%20down%20as%20Canada's%20prime%20minister%2C%20didn't%20hold%20back%20on%20X%2C%20retorting%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20isn't%20a%20snowball's%20chance%20in%20hell%20that%20Canada%20would%20become%20part%20of%20the%20United%20States.%E2%80%9D%20Elon%20Musk%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20ever%20eager%20to%20stir%20the%20pot%2C%20responded%20sarcastically%3A%20%E2%80%9CGirl%2C%20you're%20not%20the%20governor%20of%20Canada%20anymore%2C%20so%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20you%20say.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20banter%20may%20be%20entertaining%2C%20but%20the%20stakes%20of%20such%20a%20suggestion%20are%20no%20laughing%20matter.%20This%20is%20the%20k